</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Boeing Delivers Last Planes of Decade: Boeing Commercial Airplanes delivered 
its final plane of the decade last week -- a 747-400 to Lufthansa German 
Airlines. The plane was turned over to Lufthansa officials at Boeing's Everett, 
Wash., facility, a company spokesman said. Earlier in the day, USAir received a 
737-400, which Boeing said was its last domestic airline delivery of the 1980s. 
Boeing said it delivered 2,370 airplanes during the decade, including 283 this 
year. 
</P>
