<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY EARNINGS: NU-MED REPORTS LOSS OF $2.89 MILLION FOR QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Nu-Med Inc., an Encino operator of hospitals and other health-care facilities, 
said it lost $2.89 million in its fiscal second quarter, compared with a 
$703,000 profit a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
The loss came as Nu-Med's revenue for the quarter that ended Oct. 31 showed 
virtually no change, at $65.5 million, compared with a year ago. Nu-Med blamed 
the loss on several factors, including higher operating costs, lack of revenue 
gains and increased interest expense on its debt. 
</P>
<P>
For the first half of its fiscal year, Nu-Med lost $1.85 million compared with 
a $5.54-million profit a year ago. Its six-month revenue rose to $139.4 million 
from $130.1 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
