<P>
VALLEY ROUNDUP: GENETIC TESTING GROUPS AGREE TO TENTATIVE MERGER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
American Cytogenetics in North Hollywood said it reached a tentative agreement 
to merge its Diagenetics Laboratories Inc. unit with Odyssey Biomedical, a 
newly formed New York company. 
</P>
<P>
Both Diagenetics, based in West Paterson, N.J., and Odyssey Biomedical provide 
genetic testing services, the most common of which is amniocentesis, which 
helps identify genetic defects and other problems in fetuses. 
</P>
<P>
American Cytogenetics, which also provides testing services for cancer and 
other diseases, is still negotiating terms of the proposed merger, said 
American Cytogenetics President Allen Manzano. 
</P>
</TEXT>
