<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: YEAR-END LISTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DANIEL CERONE, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
News Ratings: Staff members of all-news station KFWB have ranked the Berlin 
Wall/crumbling of Communism the No. 1 news story of 1989. In the station's new 
poll, News 98 staffers ranked the Bay Area earthquake, Chinese democracy 
movement and Exxon Valdez oil spill the second-through-fourth top stories of 
'89. Tied for fifth place was the abortion debate, the Oliver North conviction 
and sentencing and the trial of Zsa Zsa Gabor. KFWB also voted an unofficial 
"Male Newsmaker of the Year" award to Mikhail Gorbachev, with Jim Bakker, 
Oliver North and Richard Ramirez tied for second place. Staffers deemed that 
the hands-down "Female Newsmaker of the Year" was Zsa Zsa Gabor. DANIEL CERONE 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
