<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Indianapolis Colt rookie wide receiver Andre Rison was on his way home to 
Flint, Mich., for Christmas when he was charged with reckless driving in Ft. 
Wayne, Ind. 
</P>
<P>
Rison was driving his 1989 Mercedes when he was stopped about 5:30 a.m. near 
Ft. Wayne. Police said he was driving 128 m.p.h. on Interstate 69. The speed 
limit is 55 m.p.h. on the interstate near the city. 
</P>
<P>
He was taken to the Allen County Lockup where he posted $500 bond and was 
released. 
</P>
</TEXT>
