<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: 1990 ORANGE COUNTY. CHALLENGE FOR THE 1990S; 
</P>
<P>
COMMUNITY LEADERS WERE ASKED WHAT WILL BE THE BIGGEST SINGLE CHALLENGE FACING 
ORANGE COUNTY IN THE NEXT DECADES AND ALSO THEIR TOP FIVE ISSUES. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Housing: "Decent, affordable housing. The county's real estate continues to 
appreciate, making housing (that is) affordable to low-and-moderate-(income) 
families almost impossible to find. Local governments, responding to the 
demands of voters, appear timid about requiring low-cost housing in their 
jurisdictions."-Mary Anne Galdo, Housing specialist with the Orange County 
Human Relations Commission 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Top 5 Issues 
</P>
<P>
Homelessness/ affordable housing. 
</P>
<P>
Health care. 
</P>
<P>
Transportation. 
</P>
<P>
Prejudice toward minority groups. 
</P>
<P>
Immigration. 
</P>
</TEXT>
