<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN JUAN CAPISTRANO AGAIN IS HOTTEST CITY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Once again, Orange County on Monday claimed the highest temperature in the 
continental United States. 
</P>
<P>
And once again, that temperature was recorded at San Juan Capistrano -- 84 
degrees. The city claimed the same honor, with a temperature of 82, on Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Monday's warm, dry weather topped off a beautiful Southern California Christmas 
weekend, with temperatures that broke records throughout the area, while most 
other parts of the country suffered with extreme cold. Example: Milo, Me., 
which recorded 22 below Monday, the lowest temperature any place in the 
contiguous 48 states. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
HOT WEATHER; SAN JUAN CAPISTRANO (CA) 
</P>
