<HEADLINE>
<P>
BALBOA FIRE KILLS WOMAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEWPORT BEACH 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 57-year-old woman was found dead in her bed early Monday after a fire swept 
through the maid's quarters of a Balboa Island home, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The woman, Law Kwui Ching, was a housekeeper who occupied separate living 
quarters in a home at 608 S. Bay Front, Newport Beach fire officials said. The 
owners of the house live in Los Angeles and were not at the home when the fire 
occurred, about 5 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
Investigators said the blaze appeared to have started accidently, caused by 
either cooking utensils or candles. Damage to the home was estimated at 
$140,000, mostly from smoke. 
</P>
<P>
Dr. Daniel Stringer, who lives across the street from the residence, said he 
was awakened by the screams of a neighbor who saw the flames. Stinger said 
Ching had come from Hong Kong about 20 years ago. 
</P>
<P>
Although a cause of death has not been determined, authorities said it is 
likely she died of smoke inhalation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Firefighter inspects scene of Balboa Island blaze. RICHARD KOEHLER / Los 
Angeles Times 
</P>
