<HEADLINE>
<P>
STALLED CAR HIT; MAN FATALLY HURT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
IRVINE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A San Gabriel man died early Sunday in Western Medical Center-Santa Ana of 
injuries suffered shortly before, when a stalled car was struck as he and two 
other men were pushing it along a Santa Ana Freeway off-ramp in Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
The man's identity was withheld pending notification of relatives, according to 
the Orange County coroner's office. 
</P>
<P>
The victim was pushing a Chevrolet by an open door on the Culver Drive off-ramp 
when the vehicle was hit by a Dodge driven by Young Ko, 41, of Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
The dead man's two companions were also injured and taken to area hospitals. 
</P>
<P>
Ko suffered internal injuries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
