<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN KILLED AS TRUCK HITS RIG 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Fountain Valley man was killed Sunday morning when his truck hit a 
tractor-trailer parked on Euclid Street, according to Sgt. Don Nielsen of the 
Fountain Valley Police Department. 
</P>
<P>
Arturo Lawrence Gonzalez, 25, was traveling south on Euclid west of Camelia 
Avenue when his four-wheel-drive truck veered to the right and crashed. 
</P>
<P>
The operator of the tractor-trailer, who was asleep in the vehicle when it was 
hit, was not injured, Nielsen said. 
</P>
<P>
Gonzalez died at the scene, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
There were no witnesses, and the cause of the accident is under investigation. 
</P>
