<HEADLINE>
<P>
EDISON SECOND IN BASKETBALL POLL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mater Dei High School remains the top-ranked team in the Orange County 
Sportswriters' Assn. prep basketball poll while Edison jumps from fourth last 
week to second following a victory over Capistrano Valley. 
</P>
<P>
Mater Dei (8-1) was idle last week and opens play this week in the Orange 
Holiday Tournament at Chapman College as the top-seeded team. 
</P>
<P>
Capistrano Valley (8-2) was ranked second last week but fell to third after an 
82-59 loss to Edison. El Toro jumps from seventh to fourth after winning three 
consecutive games at Carson City, Nev. 
</P>
<P>
Only two teams, Tustin (9-0) and Loara (8-0), remain undefeated after three 
weeks of play. The writers' poll: 
</P>
