<TEXT>
<P>
The Bush Administration today announced an emergency $500,000 package of 
humanitarian aid to Romania, after recognizing its provisional government. 
</P>
<P>
White House spokesman Marlin Fitzwater said the $500,000 in aid will be made 
available by the U.S. Agency for International Development to the International 
Red Cross. He said further U.S. aid also is likely. 
</P>
<P>
Romania has been devastated by bitter street battles between the army and 
security forces loyal to its deposed dictator. 
</P>
<P>
A hot line is being set up today at the State Department to handle the many 
calls from Americans and Romanians wanting to donate food and medicine. 
</P>
<P>
Diplomats at the U.S. Embassy in Bucharest have already been in touch with the 
new government to arrange safe passage for 42 government personnel and their 
dependents who were evacuated Sunday to neighboring Bulgaria. 
