<P>
WILD-CARD 'SEASON' WILL OPEN SUNDAY WITH A DOUBLE-HEADER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The NFL announced its playoff schedule today for the wild-card games and 
divisional round of games. 
</P>
<P>
On Sunday, the wild-card double-header opens at 9:30 a.m. PST with the NFC game 
as the Rams (11-5) play at Philadelphia (11-5). That will be followed by the 
AFC game at 1 p.m. PST with Pittsburgh (9-7) playing at Houston (9-7). 
</P>
<P>
The divisional playoffs are set for the weekend of Jan. 6 and 7. On Saturday 
Jan. 6, AFC East champ Buffalo (9-7), plays at AFC Central champ Cleveland 
(9-6-1), starting at 9:30 a.m. PST. If Philadelphia wins the NFC wild 
card-game, it will then play NFC West champ San Francisco (14-2) at 1 p.m. If 
Los Angeles wins the wild card, the 49ers' first playoff opponent will be NFC 
Central champ Minnesota (10-6). 
</P>
<P>
The lineup for Sunday, Jan. 7, has either Los Angeles or Minnesota playing the 
NFC East champion New York Giants (12-4) at 9:30 a.m. PST, followed by the AFC 
wild-card winner, either Houston or Pittsburgh, at AFC West champion Denver 
(11-5). 
</P>
</TEXT>
