<P>
WBL ALL-STARS WIN IN BELGIUM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
OOSTENDE, Belgium 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The World Basketball League All-Star team won its second straight Belgium 
International Tournament, sweeping three games over the weekend. 
</P>
<P>
The WBL edged host SunAir 91-89 Christmas night as Illinois Express teammates 
Alfredrick Hughes and Andrew Moten had 20 and 14 points, respectively, and 
Willie Bland of the Youngstown Pride added 15. 
</P>
</TEXT>
