<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
COLORADO COACH MUM ON PACT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services12/26/89 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Colorado Coach Bill McCartney says he is willing to talk with university 
officials about renegotiating his contract, but he will not discuss it with the 
news media. 
</P>
<P>
McCartney and his team are in Miami preparing for their Orange Bowl showdown 
New Year's night with Notre Dame. If the Buffs win, they will be national 
champions. 
</P>
<P>
University President Gordon Gee has said he wants to renegotiate McCartney's 
contract after the season. The eight-year coach is in the third year of a 
four-year contract, but McCartney has gone on record as saying he does not want 
to extend his contract until it runs out. 
</P>
<P>
He said, however, that if university officials want to talk about a new 
contract, he will listen. 
</P>
<P>
"Obviously, if any of my bosses want to talk to me, I'll talk to them, just 
like anyone would," McCartney said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
